<br>
Im a 46 druid and while I am not sure how much time exactly (maybe around 8 hours) I spent there I did actually get 2 full yellow bulbs of exp and about 400pp in loot.  Lots of opals dropped, as well as some black pearls, and goblin forged armor.<br>
<br>
Usually I would start with Omar the Tent Guy, follow that by the two house boys.  Then I would hug the north wall and try and target Maitre D, but that usually resulted in agroing the closest one under the arches (by the way that is a warder PH and that was the one that gave up the shroud as well).  Then I would come back and get Maitre D.  By that time it was usually about time for Omar to spawn again, so I would med up, rebuff and start over.<br>
<br>
I had ES Arms, so mana usually was not an issue.<br>
<br>
I also had the Warder spawn in place of one of the hall wanders.  The only time I would kill a hall wanderer is if it was a stonechanter or blightcaller, as these would chain cast heals on whatever else I was killing.  Also if a stonechanter or blightcaller was Omar or the houseboys, they went down first since they will heal others.<br>
<br>
Stalagknights cast a nasty 300pt dd as soon as they are agro'd.  Then they just try to cast engulfing darkness, so no worries there.<br>
<br>
Good luck and thanks for the great info.<br>
